rComments: Professeur connaissant extrêmement bien les rudiments et théories sociologiques. Quoi que quelque peu monotone lors de ses présentations en classe, il demeure un bon professeur si vous écoutez ce qu'il dit avec attention. Il est stricte mais honnête dans sa correction et il fut présent pour m'aider lorsque j'avais des questions (à son bureau).
Very nice man, crystal clear.  He doesn't seem tolerant with bad and average students.  Just listen what he's talking about and you'll learn a lot.
Excellent prof. exigeant mais juste.  Il faut travailler dans son cours pour réussir et bien connaître le français.

This prof has no charisma what so ever and is very boring to listen to. He also seems to lack interest in his students and usually leaves as soon as he can after class. He's an extremely tough and unfair grader. Avoid this professor if you can.
Tres gentil, mais peut-etre trop intelligent pour etre un prof de troisieme annee. Si tu ecoute bien, et tu travail fort, tu vais avoir un bonne note

He would sit at his desk for 90 minutes and stare at his notes speaking in a completely monotonous tone. he would never pause after giving a definition so you could write it down or repeat anything that might be important, he had no consideration for the few anglophones in the class and just seemed to want to leave as fast as possible. worst prof.
One of the best prof at UO.  He's very knowledgable but he's a tough grader.
He's not too bad, he talks a lot (without visual aids) and really knows his stuff. He sometimes wanders off out of subject but usually notices and comes right back.
